<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
    Network security config for ElleAnn.

    IMPORTANT — why cleartext is permitted globally here:

    Android's <domain-config> is HOSTNAME-ORIENTED. It matches specific hostnames
    or subdomains — it is NOT CIDR-range-aware. "192.168.0.0" as a domain entry
    only matches the literal string "192.168.0.0", not any subnet range.
    The previous version of this file was conceptually correct in intent but
    technically wrong in implementation. This version is honest.

    Because the ElleAnn server IP is user-defined at pair time and is always on a
    private LAN (never reachable from the internet), we permit cleartext globally.
    This is the standard approach for closed LAN companion apps where:
      1. The server is always on a local network under user control
      2. The app makes zero external internet requests
      3. TLS on a LAN IP without a CA cert creates worse UX than cleartext

    If TLS is added to the Elle server in a future build, remove this base-config
    and add a <domain-config> pointing to the paired IP with certificate pinning.

    Apache (port 8080, Named Pipes SQL) and REST (port 8000) are both covered.
-->
<network-security-config>
    <base-config cleartextTrafficPermitted="true">
        <trust-anchors>
            <certificates src="system" />
        </trust-anchors>
    </base-config>
</network-security-config>
